SUMMARY:Abundance in Bloom: A Harvest Team Reception and Benefit with gues
 t Ashley C. Ford
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260414T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260414T180000
UID:ai1ec-148076-94771@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Each spring\, Mother Hubbard’s Cupboard gathers to grow and 
 celebrate our Harvest Team\, a giving society whose recurring contribution
 s to our work ensure we are a stable\, reliable resource for our community
 . We are again thrilled to invite you to gather – and to strengthen our 
 community of donors who make our mission possible. Please join us. This ye
 ar\, we have a special guest joining us: Indiana writer andNew York Timesb
 estselling author Ashley C. Ford will share brief remarks on community and
  care.Space is limited.Reserve your spot today.​
LOCATION:Devault Alumni Center\, 1000 East 17th Street\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/abundance-in-bloom-a-harvest-team-reception-and
 -benefit-with-guest-ashley-c-ford/?instance_id=94771
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:CSIU Candidate Forum on Science\, Technology\, and the Environment
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260414T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260414T183000
UID:ai1ec-147840-94897@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:The forum\, which is one of the nation’s only candidate foru
 ms with a focus on science-related policy\, will feature five of the six c
 andidates registered for the election for Indiana’s 9th Congressional Di
 strict: Jim Graham (D)\, Brad Meyer (D)\, Tim Peck (D)\, Keil Roark (D)\, 
 and Floyd Taylor (I). Incumbent Representative Erin Houchin (R) was invite
 d\, but unable to attend. The event is open to the public.The forum is cos
 ponsored by CSIU’s student affiliate organization\, Advocates for Scienc
 e @IU\, the League of Women Voters of Bloomington/Monroe County\, Citizens
 ’ Climate Lobby of South Central Indiana\, and the Green Sanctuary Task 
 Force of the Unitarian Universalist Church of Bloomington.For those unable
  to participate in person\, the forum will also be live streamed at the AS
 IU YouTube channel:https://www.youtube.com/@AdvocatesforScienceatIUFor add
 itional information\, contact us at[email protected].
LOCATION:Auditorium\, Monroe County Public Library\, 303 E Kirkwood Ave\, 
 Meeting Rooms 1B/1C on the ground floor\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/csiu-candidate-forum-on-science-technology-and-
 the-environment/?instance_id=94897
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
