BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Oklahoma!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260417T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260417T213000
UID:ai1ec-148155-94791@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Oklahoma was the first successful production to seamlessly int
 egrate music\, dance\, and plot into a cohesive narrative—pioneering the
  use of dance to drive the story—the show is credited with launching the
  “Golden Age” of Broadway musicals and won a special Pulitzer Prize fo
 r Drama in 1944.You’re invited to join us in the lobby of the Musical Ar
 ts Center at 6:30 forOpera Insights – A Pre-show talk on Rodgers and Ham
