SUMMARY:Sycamore Land Trust’s Arbor Day Tree Giveaway
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260425T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260425T140000
UID:ai1ec-148342-94904@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Arbor Day by planting a native tree!Sycamore Land Tr
 ust\, a nonprofit conservation organization protecting over 11\,800 acres 
 in southern Indiana\, will give away more than 800 free native tree seedli
 ngs on Saturday\, April 25\, from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. at Bloomingfoods East 
 (3220 E. 3rd St.) and Bloomingfoods Near West (316 W. 6th St.) in Blooming
 ton. Available species include elderberry\, eastern redbud\, persimmon\, g
 ray dogwood\, ninebark\, and red oak. This event is sponsored by IU Health
  and co-hosted by Bloomingfoods Co-op Market. Tree seedlings were grown by
  the Indiana Department of Natural Resources. One free tree seedling per p
 erson while supplies last. Learn more atsycamorelandtrust.org/free-trees.
LOCATION:Bloomingfoods Co-op Markets\, 3220 E. 3rd St. and 316 W. 6th St.
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/sycamore-land-trusts-arbor-day-tree-giveaway/?i
 nstance_id=94904
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
