BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spring Plant Sale to Benefit Sycamore Land Trust’s Native Plant 
 Nursery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T140000
UID:ai1ec-148344-94905@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Sycamore Land Trust\, a nonprofit conservation organization pr
 otecting over 11\,800 acres in southern Indiana\, is thrilled to announce 
 their fifth annual Spring Plant Sale! They are offering over 45 species of
  plants that were homegrown in their Native Plant Nursery from seed to pla
 nt plug. Many species are grown from locally collected seed at nearby pres
 erves. All species are ethically sourced and native to southern Indiana\, 
 providing benefits to local pollinators and wildlife. All proceeds going b
 ack into nursery operations and native plant restoration projects. Stop by
  to learn from experienced staff and volunteers on the advantages of garde
 ning with native species!
LOCATION:Bloomingfoods East Parking Lot: 3220 E. 3rd St.
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/spring-plant-sale-to-benefit-sycamore-land-trus
 ts-native-plant-nursery/?instance_id=94905
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
